12:
Say, 'ave you seen Shroombo around 
these parts?
15:
...Still 'ave them otherworlders on your 
mind, do ye?
20:
Regitare!
Sorry... How long were you there?
23:
It's been quite some time since I've 
seen you this quiet for so long.
27:
Nothing... I'm fine! No problem! No 
worries!
30:
I'm a sprite of the forest! As long as 
sun is bright, I'm happy!
32:
Izzat so? Then tell me, what do ye think 
of the night?
38:
The moon is out, and I like Owlbert's 
singing!
40: And the stars... the stars are bright!
43:
That's right. You've always been 
intrigued by the stars, haven't you, 
Challua?
45:
Ow about ye join Alk and the others 
then?
51:
Not exactly. I just know you that well, 
child.
54:
You're one of me beloved forest 
children, right?
59: But I can't go. I can't leave you alone.
62:
It's not a secret, Regitare. You have 
a hole where your heart was.
65:
I mean, there isn't much between me 
ribs as of late.
71:
We forest sprites... We all know. We 
watched you when we were trees.
73:
It was your crying that woke me up, 
after thousands of years!
77:
Yes, well... I don't want to tie ye down 
to these woods, Challua.
78:
I'd hate for you to live a lonely life as 
I once did! And don't you worry about 
me. I'll be reight.
81:
Regitare... I'm happy you'll always be 
here.
84:
Thank you, Challua. But this is 
a journey ye need to take for your own 
good, methinks.
85:
You've been blessed by the great Spirit 
Tree with legs to travel and a heart full 
of love.
96:
Teach them everything ye know
about the blessings of the sun and 
nature!
115:
I kept my promise! I came to see you 
again!
119: I'm happy to see you too.
126:
I went and said all that, but... I guess 
I'm worried about her.
127:
And she ain't the only one who wants 
to see what these worlds 'ave to offer!
129:
Maybe it's time for ol' Regitare to go on 
a journey of his own...
